The paper deals with object tracking from an aerial view using computer vision techniques, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) communities. The proposed approach involves learning a new type of correlation filter, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques in object tracking, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
